[[ConfigureTwilioforAPIAccess-ConfigureTwilioforAPIAccess]]
= Configure Twilio for API Access

Twilio is a cloud communications Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS). It
provides an API for making and receiving telephone calls, and sending
and receiving text messages. To get started with Twilio, follow the
steps below to gain access to their free sandbox service to send SMS
text-messages. You can then configure the Twilio connector in Mule
Studio with your API credentials.

[[ConfigureTwilioforAPIAccess-CreateaNewTwilioAccount]]
== Create a New Twilio Account

1.  To create a new Twilio account, go to
https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio and register under "Try Twillio Free".

[[ConfigureTwilioforAPIAccess-ObtainAPICredentials]]
== Obtain API Credentials

1.  Once you login to your developer account, you'll see the Twilio
dashboard. Note the *Account SID* and *Auth Token* values provided. You
will need to copy these credentials into the Twilio connector
configuration menu in Mule Studio. +

image:/documentation/download/attachments/66060979/TwilioSetup1.png?version=1&modificationDate=1339025645594[image]

[[ConfigureTwilioforAPIAccess-VerifyaSMS-EnabledPhone]]
== Verify a SMS-Enabled Phone

1.  With a free developer account, you will need to verify your
SMS-enabled phone before you can send text messages to it.
2.  Click on *Numbers* in the Twilio website navigation to go to the
Manage Numbers portion of their website.
3.  Click on **Verify Numbers**, and then click on **Verify a number**.
A new window will open as shown below. +

image:/documentation/download/attachments/66060979/TwilioSetup2.png?version=1&modificationDate=1339015180213[image]
4.  Enter your cell phone number, and click on **Call this number**.
Follow their instructions provided to validate your number. You will
receive an automated phone call and need to enter an authorization code.
5.  Finally, to send SMS-messages, you will need to use the Sandbox
"from" number. This phone number needs to be entered into the Twilio
connector configuration menu in Mule Studio. This Sandbox number is also
located on the Twilio dashboard, along with the Account SID and Auth
Token. +

image:/documentation/download/attachments/66060979/TwilioSetup3.png?version=1&modificationDate=1339026061654[image]

